  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Protecting and Supporting Human Rights Defenders in Colombia- Closure and Consolidation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This projects seeks to consolidate the activities of a Colombian component of a project that aims to support and protect human right defenders at risk working on land and environmental rights in Latin America, with a focus on Colombia and Guatemala.  Following the significant increase in the number of human rights defenders killed, threatened, stigmatised and criminalised across Latin America. The project will consolidate and support efforts to provide urgent protection and capacity strengthening of human rights defenders at risk working in remote rural areas and to enable their cases to be heard at national and international level through advocacy and communications work. It has a particular focus on the most marginalised and excluded groups, namely indigenous and afro-descendent communities.</narrative>
  </description>
